  • Method Details

    • readData

      void readData(SimpleObjectInputStream in) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException, InstantiationException, IllegalAccessException
      Read object from the data stream.

      Note other exceptions such as ClassCastException or NullPointerException and others could be thrown if the order of writeData() calls does not match the corresponding readData() calls for the same classes.

      Parameters:
      in - the input stream, never null
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs or if this input stream has reached the end.
      ClassNotFoundException - if the class cannot be located
      IllegalAccessException - if the class or its nullary constructor is not accessible.
      InstantiationException - if this Class represents an abstract class, an interface, an array class, a primitive type, or void; or if the class has no nullary constructor; or if the instantiation fails for some other reason.
      See Also:
      • SimpleObjectInputStream.readObject()

    • writeData

      void writeData(SimpleObjectOutputStream out) throws IOException
      Write the object to the data stream. This method handles the serialization to recreate the state of this object.
      Parameters:
      out - the output stream, never null
      Throws:
      IOException - Any exception thrown by the underlying OutputStream.
      See Also:
      • SimpleObjectOutputStream.writeObject(org.opensextant.giscore.utils.IDataSerializable)
